race.comment: EMPIRE OF PAIN (1) comes through a strong race behind Enchanted Jenni here who is on a three-run winning streak, just edged out late after looking the winner in the straight before the other horse kicked back. This looks a winnable affair, she can roll forward and take catching again. PHAROAH'S GLORY (8) has won two in a row, dominant at Ballarat last time over 1400m when scoring by three lengths. Up in grade but the rise in trip should suit and she can measure up strongly. TEMPRANILLO (10) was behind EMPIRE OF PAIN last time from a tricky gate in a race that didn't really suit. The win prior was solid and she gets the golden switch to barrier one here. NAINA (2) is coming off a narrow win over ON BROADWAY (4), the latter of whom has won since. Both have each-way claims.
